  <div class="policy-header">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 6, 2026</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>The Trainer Ops ("we," "us," or "our") is a fitness business management app currently in development. Our website is <a href="https://thetrainerops.com">thetrainerops.com</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What information we collect</h2>
    <p>When you join our waitlist, we collect only your email address. We do not collect payment information, health data, or any other personal information at this time.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <p>Your email is used solely to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Notify you when the app launches</li>
      <li>Send occasional updates about development progress</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">We will never spam you.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or share your email with third parties. If we use an email platform (such as Beehiiv) to manage the waitlist, that platform may store your email on our behalf under their own privacy policy.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>You can request to be removed from our waitlist at any time by emailing <a href="mailto:thetrainerops@gmail.com">thetrainerops@gmail.com</a>. We will delete your information within 7 days.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>California residents (CalOPPA)</h2>
    <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal data we collect and to request its deletion. To exercise this right, contact us at the email above.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>If our data practices change, we will update this page and revise the "Last updated" date.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Jennifer Lee<br>
